BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:VbqlvScsBKIoV5fHGP7L8
SUMMARY:SafeCampus Violence Prevention and Response Training
DTSTAMP:20260306T004548Z
DTSTART:20260312T163000Z
DESCRIPTION:Thursday\, Mar 12\, 2026\, 9:30 - 11 a.m. PDT\n\nDuring this in
	teractive training\, we ask participants to consider their unique role in 
	preventing violence at the University of Washington. This training has bee
	n adapted to consider the remote academic environments that many staff\, s
	tudents\, and faculty are currently experiencing. We will explore mental h
	ealth and warning signs of different forms of violence including\; workpla
	ce violence\, relationship violence\, sexual harassment\, and stalking. We
	 will briefly practice in-person and remote bystander intervention techniq
	ues and build your understanding of UW resources.\n\nClick the link below 
	to register for this training.\n\nCampus room: Online Zoom Training Access
	ibility Contact:  safecampus@uw.edu Event Types: Information Sessions\, Le
	ctures/Seminars\, Workshops More info:  forms.office.com…\n\nhttps://seato
	day.6amcity.com/events/#/details/safecampus-violence-prevention-and-respon
	se-training/17922579/2026-03-12T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/safecampus-violence-preve
	ntion-and-response-training/17922579/2026-03-12T00
LOCATION:University of Washington\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
